id: pm-kr3t
title: "Beyond-PM SDK exemplar phase 2: temporal digital-twin graph with entity relationships, event replay, point-in-time state, and invariants"
description: "Prove the public pm SDK can model a non-PM digital twin whose entities, relationships, immutable events, snapshots, invariants, and queries are implemented without CLI-internal imports."
type: Feature
status: closed
priority: 4
tags[7]: "area:sdk",digital-twin,exemplar,graph,history,long-term,non-pm
created_at: "2026-07-13T22:00:59.149Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-23T11:27:45.317Z"
closed_at: "2026-07-23T11:27:00.553Z"
author: codex-root
estimated_minutes: 900
acceptance_criteria: "Choose and document one bounded domain such as a facility, production cell, fleet, supply network, or service topology with entities, typed relationships, states, commands, events, and invariants; Implement the exemplar entirely through published SDK exports and extension or package contracts; no CLI internal, core internal, or tracker-file access is allowed; Every mutation appends attributable immutable events; rebuilding from genesis and from verified checkpoints yields identical state and relationship indexes; Queries support current and point-in-time entity state, topology and impact traversal, event history, provenance, invariant violations, and bounded shell-friendly export; Model concurrent observations, conflicting updates, corrections by superseding events, schema evolution, offline or federated replicas, and deterministic merge or explicit conflict surfaces; Property and scenario tests cover replay, temporal relationships, invariant enforcement, partial failure, restore, import and export, and tamper evidence; Publish a structured gap report that links every missing capability to the existing SDK promotion lineage or a duplicate-checked new item"
goal: Universal project and context primitives through the public pm SDK
objective: "Validate that SDK item, field, relationship, event, query, history, and replay primitives can represent a realistic evolving physical or business system"
value: Provides concrete proof that pm SDK abstractions generalize to digital twins and exposes missing primitives before they ossify
impact: "Broadens the SDK from project tracking to event-sourced domain engines, simulations, asset networks, organizations, and business logic"
outcome: "An installable exemplar package, realistic fixture, point-in-time queries, invariant evaluation, replay proof, and SDK gap report"
why_now: "The roadmap explicitly targets VCS and company-scale logic, but digital-twin capability has no canonical tracked exemplar"
parent: pm-8ngt
risk: high
confidence: low
resolution: "Shipped @unbrained/pm-digital-twin as a first-party, public-SDK-only exemplar backed by host-injected graph/event primitives and no runtime private imports."
expected_result: "A clean consumer can install a digital-twin package, create custom facility entities, append and replay temporal state/topology, evaluate invariants and impact, reconcile offline streams, and export/import verified checkpoints through public SDK contracts."
actual_result: "The package provides seven domain commands, two custom item types, five fields, four relationship kinds, event-time replay, corrections/conflicts/schema evolution, graph invariants and impact, offline merge, checkpointed bounded bundles, transactional creation/compensation, complete docs, clean installed CLI proof, and 100% coverage."
