close_reason: "Delivered the public-SDK-only temporal digital-twin package with custom schema, immutable events, point-in-time replay, topology/invariants, impact, replica merge, checkpoints, import/export, installed CLI proof, docs, and 100% coverage."
body: "## Suggested domain\n\nA small production facility is a useful stress test: sites contain lines; lines contain machines and sensors; assets depend on utilities and upstream processes; observations and maintenance commands change state; work orders and incidents connect operational context; safety and capacity rules are temporal invariants.\n\n## Capabilities exercised\n\nCustom item and event types; custom relationship registry; immutable command and observation history; derived snapshots and indexes; point-in-time reconstruction; topology and blast-radius graph queries; constraints and invariants; identity and authorship; schema migrations; import, export, merge, and federation; compact terminal output.\n\n## Boundary\n\nThis is an exemplar and conformance test, not a production industrial-control system. It must reveal SDK gaps without moving domain-specific policy into core."
